The paper deals with finding maximum-cardinality matchings in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on cocomparability graphs, which are a subclass of perfect graphs that includes interval graphs and permutation graphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, given that the paper presents a linear-time algorithm, it is most likely to belong to cs.DS, followed by cs.DM and cs.CG. The other two categories, cs.GT and cs.LG, are less likely as they are not directly related to the problem of finding maximum-cardinality matchings.
